From: jackyzy823 <jackyzy823@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 17:10:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/7] fix(tests): pass TestClientAuthPublicKey

Since https://github.com/zmap/zgrab2/pull/616, "ext-info-c" won't be
sent if `CollectExtensions` is false.

As a result, server wouldn't announce the support of rsa-sha2-256.

Ref: https://github.com/golang/crypto/commit/6fad3dfc18918c2ac9c112e46b32473bd2e5e2f9#diff-5d70d3dfd7a5a1e978a852be04260c37b5aa12e44492bd54f470846f2278f07eR627-R634
---
 lib/ssh/client_auth_test.go | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/lib/ssh/client_auth_test.go b/lib/ssh/client_auth_test.go
index e986926..8cb5d9f 100644
--- a/lib/ssh/client_auth_test.go
+++ b/lib/ssh/client_auth_test.go
@@ -128,6 +128,9 @@ func TestClientAuthPublicKey(t *testing.T) {
 			PublicKeys(signer),
 		},
 		HostKeyCallback: InsecureIgnoreHostKey(),
+		Config: Config{
+			CollectExtensions: true,
+		},
 	}
 	if err := tryAuth(t, config); err != nil {
 		t.Fatalf("unable to dial remote side: %s", err)
-- 
